column43: get rid of the jargon, use plain English, stop assuming millions of Australians are each experts in tax affairs. You should not be building this app AT ALL. you should be getting a private, TRUSTED, third-party who is NOT our government to be helping us with our taxes. (and I strongly suspect they would do a better job, at probably 10x less expense, than our ATO as well, for what it's worth). I pay tax for my government to run my country. I do NOT appreciate my tax being spent to pay the public service to steal jobs and opportunity from Australian private business and compete against us for accounting products. You are actively DESTROYING the opportunity for innovative Australian business to create worldwide solutions with this idea of yours.

column43: Firstly, I would like to appreciate ATO for making this app and improving it. Unfortunately, it is the different jargon used with for same definition that confuses people. For example, 'Cash flow position' in this case is Income - Expenses for that period. However, according to my accountant it is money available in my business bank account with might include money received from previous month. I understand it can be tricky to make everyone understand. So my suggestion would be to have 'glossary' for all the terminologies and jargon used on this app. Maybe along with examples! Just a suggestion :) Keep the good work going!
